<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHERIFF'S OFFICER IS FIRED AS INMATE RIDES AWAY IN STYLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A sheriff's lieutenant was fired because a jail inmate escaped and rode away 
in a limousine, the officer's lawyer said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jonathan Merino left the Medina County Jail on Jan. 29 while on an 
work-release program and arranged for a limousine to pick him up. Merino, 
facing charges of passing bad checks and forgery, was last seen in Cleveland 
that day. 
</P>
<P>
 Attorney Richard Marco said his client, Lt. John Detchon, plans to appeal his 
dismissal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
