<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASEANA WINS THE SANTA MARGARITA, HER FIRST VICTORY AS A 7-YEAR-OLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paseana won her first race as a 7-year-old and moved from seventh to fifth 
place on the female money list Sunday with a 2 3/4-length victory in the 
$300,000 Santa Margarita Handicap, a stake that the Argentine-bred mare also 
won in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Carrying 123 pounds, four to nine pounds more than her opponents, Paseana and 
jockey Chris McCarron came from fourth to overtake Stalcreek in the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
 Winning for the 17th time in 29 starts, the two-time Eclipse Award winner 
earned $180,000, increasing her total to $2.8 million. Dance Smartly, Lady's 
Secret, All Along and Bayakoa, all retired, are ahead of her in purses, with 
Dance Smartly No. 1 at $3.2 million.  
</P>
<P>
 Trainer Ron McAnally said that Paseana will run in the $500,000 Apple Blossom 
Handicap at Oaklawn Park on April 2. She is the only horse to win the Apple 
Blossom twice. BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
