"He's very confident out there and he knows his job." Carlos (.324) anchors the 
infield. He has good range and a strong enough arm to make difficult plays. 
Torres expects Moreno to provide the Colonists with several quality innings as 
their No. 1 starter. Moreno, primarily a reliever as a junior, was 2-2 with a 
3.46 earned-run average. Jimenez, Mejia and Navarrette should help make up a 
quality pitching staff. "We'll have to scrap for our runs," Torres said, "but 
