second-place finish in league play last season. He lost his entire varsity 
roster of the previous season to graduation. Before 1993, the Tigers won or 
shared the championship three consecutive seasons. Brea-Olinda, which has eight 
returning starters, is poised to make another run at the league title. "Unlike 
last season, our experience is our biggest asset this year," Hiskey said. 
"We've got to replace some people, but we have young guys who should help." 
Brambilla, a first-team, all-league selection, batted .375 with six home runs 
and 23 runs batted in. Theis and Stoddard are strong defensively, and Hiskey 
believes they will also make big contributions at the plate. "We've got a lot 
of guys who have been through battles before," Hiskey said. "That's a lot more 
than we could say last year." 
</P>
<P>
