<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; NOMINATIONS SOUGHT FOR CITY ARTS AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cypress Cultural Arts Commission is seeking nominations for its 
Outstanding Contribution to the Arts Award, which is given to a volunteer who 
has benefited the arts in the community. 
</P>
<P>
 Nominations are due by 5 p.m. March 25, and the award recipient will be 
announced at a reception May 5 during the city's eighth annual "Cypress 
Celebrates the Arts" week, which will take place April 29 through May 
6.Applications are available at the Cypress Community Center, 5700 Orange 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner will receive a plaque and a commendation by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's winner, Christine Swain, donated time and her own artwork to 
schools and organizations to raise money for worthwhile local programs, said 
Nancy Bruns, recreation coordinator of the Cypress Recreation and Park 
District. 
</P>
<P>
 The award "honors volunteers who put so much time into the arts and bringing 
the arts to the people of Cypress so they can enjoy all different forms of 
art," Bruns said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two to six nominations have been received in each of the six years since the 
award was first bestowed. "There's a lot of work done by volunteers for the 
arts programs in the city," Bruns said, adding that she hopes the panel will 
receive more nominations this year. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 229-6780.MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
