<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; ST. PATRICK'S PARADE GETS FAMILY THEME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The International Year of the Family will be the theme of the city's 25th 
annual St. Patrick's Day Parade on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Parade floats will emphasize the world's rich cultural diversity by honoring 
families from different backgrounds and heritages.Special recognition will also 
be given to organizers of the first St. Patrick's Day parade in Mission Viejo 
and to the U.S. World Cup Soccer team. 
</P>
<P>
 Original organizers Tom Mitchel, Bob Ramsey and Bob Brennon and their families 
will ride in a special yellow fire engine. Another special float will transport 
the soccer team, which trains in Mission Viejo and will compete in the World 
Cup this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 100 floats, youth groups and horse troupes are expected to 
participate in the parade, which will start on Olympiad Road at 11 a.m. The 
parade route will run from Olympiad Road to Marguerite Parkway, then end at 
Alicia Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the parade, call (714) 830-7066. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
