<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SPOT OPEN ON CITY DEVELOPMENT PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents interested in filling a vacancy on the city Economic Development 
Commission can apply for the position through March 16. 
</P>
<P>
 One seat is open on the commission, which helps bring new business into the 
community and develops the city's economic resources. 
</P>
<P>
 A brief application form can be picked up at the city clerk's office in City 
Hall, 26522 La Alameda. Applications must be returned to the city clerk by 5 
p.m. March 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Commission members must be registered voters and Mission Viejo residents. The 
commission consists of five members who are appointed by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the city clerk's office at (714) 348-2052. FRANK 
MESSINA 
