<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; COLLEGE TO HOLD SAT PREPARATION CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College will offer Scholastic Aptitude Test preparation 
classes for college-bound students starting Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The classes will be held Tuesdays and Thursdays from March 8 to 17. 
</P>
<P>
 All parts of the test will be covered, including sections on antonyms, 
sentence completion, reading passages and mathematical sections. 
</P>
<P>
 Test-taking strategies will also be examined, spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The $70 fee for the series includes the Baron SAT test preparation manual and 
related materials. 
</P>
<P>
 Classes will be held from 4 to 6:30 p.m. in Room D-107 at the Santa Ana 
campus, at 17th and Bristol streets. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 564-6220. JON NALICK 
