ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SADDLEBACK DISTRICT GETS 2 TOP OFFICIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback Community College District has a new chancellor and Saddleback 
College has a new president. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees last week signed former chancellor Robert A. Lombardi to a three-year 
contract at an annual salary of $145,000 plus benefits and expenses, returning 
him to the post he left in 1981.He replaces Richard Sneed, who retired in 
September. 
</P>
<P>
 Ned Doffoney was signed to a two-year contract as Saddleback College president 
at a $92,225 annual salary plus benefits and expenses. 
</P>
<P>
 Lombardi left the district to enter the private sector but for the last three 
years has been chancellor of College of the Sequoias, a community college 
district in Visalia in the San Joaquin Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Doffoney succeeds Constance M. Carroll, who resigned in December, 1992, to 
become president of Mesa College in San Diego. He comes to Saddleback with 20 
years of experience as an administrator. Since 1990, he has been acting vice 
president of academic affairs at Los Angeles City College. 
</P>
