<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SILVER STRAND; MAN HELD IN ALLEGED 
KIDNAP-MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 43-year-old Silver Strand man has been arrested on suspicion of kidnaping, 
child molestation, false imprisonment and producing child pornography in a case 
involving two children, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's investigators arrested Jack Steven Sobonya at his home in the 
unincorporated beach community Saturday after the children's parents contacted 
deputies, Senior Deputy Joe Evans said. 
</P>
<P>
 Evans said Sobonya allegedly befriended the children, ages 12 and 9, in 
February by offering to take them fishing, with the permission of their 
parents. 
</P>
<P>
 He is accused of later molesting one of the youngsters and videotaping the 
children for pornographic films. 
</P>
<P>
 Evans said one of the children told a parent about the alleged encounters 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The child's parents then contacted sheriff's deputies, who took Sobonya into 
custody. 
</P>
<P>
 Evans said Sobonya remained in custody Sunday at Ventura County Jail in lieu 
of $50,000 bail. J. E. MITCHELL 
