<P>
 The family of a Port Hueneme man critically injured in a hit-and-run accident 
is offering a $500 reward for information leading to the arrest of the driver 
responsible. 
</P>
<P>
 Russell Akuna, 34, was riding a bicycle just after midnight Feb. 27 along the 
700 block of Halyard Street in Port Hueneme when he was struck by a 
dark-colored sedan, a Port Hueneme police spokeswoman said. 
</P>
