<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; CITY MAY SEEK STATE FUNDS FOR BIKE PATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Simi Valley City Council today will consider applying for $53,000 in state 
funds to extend a city bicycle trail. 
</P>
<P>
 The money would be used to extend the Arroyo Simi Bicycle Trail from the 
Metrolink station on Los Angeles Avenue east to Corriganville Park. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved by the council, the application will be considered by the Ventura 
County Transportation Commission, which will dole out about $271,000 in state 
funds next year for pedestrian and bike projects throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
 Over the past several years, Simi Valley has used state funds for bike paths 
along the Arroyo Simi and the Kadota Fig Drain. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
