</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GM Recalls 81,900 Vehicles: The auto maker said it plans to recall the 
1994-model passenger cars, minivans and pickups to fix various safety-related 
problems.The recall covers about 49,000 Buick Century and Oldsmobile Cutlass 
Ciera models equipped with 3.1-liter engines, to fix a throttle problem. In 
addition, General Motors Corp. said is is recalling about 32,000 Chevrolet 
Lumina minivan, Pontiac Trans Sport and Oldsmobile Silhouette models to repair 
third-row seat belt retractors. The company is also recalling about 900 C/K 
half-ton short-box pickups to inspect front fuel tank bracket attachment nuts. 
</P>
