<P>
 Harding Protests Use of Photo in Ad: A potential legal brawl has emerged in 
New York over the use of Olympic figure skater Tonya Harding's photo in a 
pun-filled newspaper ad for two music bargain stores. But her lawyers pointed 
out that Harding, under investigation in the Jan. 6 attack on Nancy Kerrigan, 
has not authorized commercial use of her name or likeness. The ad in the 
current Village Voice and NY Press is for two Tower Clearance Outlets owned by 
Tower Records in New York. The photo of Harding adjoins a cartoon balloon that 
suggests she is saying, "Unbeatable bargains that will bring you to your knees. 
. . ." 
