BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Spectrum Executive Under Investigation: Peter Caserta, 51, chief executive of 
embattled Spectrum Information Technologies Inc., is under federal 
investigation for mail fraud.A federal grand jury in Brooklyn is also 
investigating Caserta Group, a business founded by Caserta in 1988, according 
to a criminal subpoena. U.S. postal inspectors are investigating claims made by 
Caserta Group to prospective clients seeking financing. Caserta's private 
organization is in the same Manhasset, N.Y., office building as Spectrum. It 
charged up to $25,000 to help find financing, according to clients. 
</P>
