<TEXT>
<P>
 Imported Vehicle Sales Up 26%: Sales of imported cars, trucks and buses in 
Japan soared in February from the year-earlier month to 17,812 units, the Japan 
Automobile Importers Assn. reported. The sharp increase in February came as an 
extension of the recent rise in foreign car sales in Japan, which are boosted 
largely by lower prices resulting from the appreciation of the yen against the 
dollar and other major currencies. 
