<P>
 Jobless Rate Revised Downward: The Bureau of Statistics updated its employment 
data for the past six months, dropping the January jobless rate to 10.5% from a 
previously reported 10.6%. The revised figure is the lowest unemployment rate 
since April, 1992. "There is a strong possibility of a sub-10% unemployment 
rate by the end of 1994," the bureau said. 
