</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Help Planned for Vietnam: The government has agreed to help Vietnam develop 
the transportation infrastructure in Hanoi, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs 
said. The two countries signed a memorandum of understanding on a 
transportation project for Hanoi, under which they will cooperate on the 
development of a traffic engineering and management system, the improvement of 
bus services and the drafting of a road code. This is the second major 
technical cooperation project for the two countries, the ministry said. 
</P>
