PACIFIC WATCH: JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Business Sentiment Index Holds Steady: The Bank of Japan's quarterly Tankan 
report, issued last week, shows that the business sentiment index -- the 
percentage of business people expecting things to get better minus those 
expecting worsening conditions -- is a level 56. The bank said corporate 
capital spending will fall 4.5% in fiscal 1994, on top of a 9.2% decline for 
1993. Meanwhile, the Construction Ministry said housing starts shot up 20.7% 
from a year ago because of low interest rates and declining prices. 
</P>
